        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 10 at 1:59PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 159 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Monument, or 16 miles northwest of Colorado Springs, moving east at
20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Northern Colorado Springs, Woodland Park, Monument, Air Force
Academy, Palmer Lake, Crystola, Gleneagle, and Black Forest.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
